The paper introduces a method for compressed sensing of diffusion MRI data, which involves exploiting the theory of compressed sensing and using a sparse representation in the domain of a linear transform. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of spatial-domain constraints to improve reconstruction accuracy, which could place it in the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) or Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.CV, and cs.LG, followed by cs.NA and cs.SI.
